name: Costa Verde Seafront Villa with Butler, Breakfast

reviews.comments: Divya and her staff were amazing!! They were flexible with check in and check out. Staff onsite were very helpful and accommodating. Location is perfect! Beautiful view of ocean and under 100 feet to get to the beach! Just keep in mind building is not super new, but they maintain it very well and for the most part you won’t even notice.
Good large Place with beach very close by. large rooms with all amenities and good poool.

Had a wonderful stay at this place. The Host, Manager, Care Taker and the Security were all so prompt and helpful. This property is very close to the beach and has a very good view from the 2nd Floor.
The only possible improvement I could think about is "Having some Indoor Games". This might add value.
Overall we all had a very satisfying and enjoyable stay.

We went as a group of 12. Had an amazing stay at this property. Rooms are spacious and well designed. The view from the 2nd floor is outstanding. Host and the caretakers are super friendly and took care of all our requirements. Was even surprised by how good the complimentary meal was.
The air conditioning wasn't effective in some of the rooms. That's something they can look into. But overall great place, will definitely recommend!

We had amazing time at Costa Verde villa! Kids enjoyed the pool so much and the property is well maintained. Rooms were spacious and bathrooms were lovely! Caretakers were very accommodative and our kids had amazing time  and requested us to extend the stay. :). Accessibility to beach and beach view from the property gave us a calming effect. It was so breezy in the second floor. Due to ambiance, we did a family photoshoot too. Overall, had a very pleasant experience!!

The place is right next to the beach .I am not sure of the name of the beach . Its a three floor Villa with bech view from 1st and 2 nd floor . Divya is a great host. Location of the house is superb. Recommended for family and friends .we enjoyed our stay.
Some cons
This place is newly getting renovated , so there are some problem in AC fan hot water in few rooms (total 5 rooms). One of the washroom is under maintenance in 2 nd floor .
Its mentioned that if required then you can call maid for cleaning. In my opinion cleaning is must . As its very near to beach the rooms gets very messy because of the wind.
So then should call cleaning staff every day else the property will surely get dirty ..
Very good place to stay at stones throw away from a private beach. Kids and adults would enjoy the place

Check in was very smooth even though i arrived early. Divya gave us a tour of the whole house. It has multiple bedrooms spread over multiple floors. Private swimming pool. Balcony in every floor overlooks the ocean. Did not realize places like these existed in Chennai. I highly recommend this place and would visit again

name: Mad about Coco (Retreat Groups/20 pax) Beach B&B

reviews.comments: A very cosy place with excellent hostess. A place to relax at. Good breakfast.

Lovely chilled place in North Cliff Varkala.  Just set back from the cliff so really convenient for everything yet still quiet.  We had one of the ac rooms.  Fairly basic but clean hot water and lovely balcony.  There's 2 nice chill out areas.  Anita was friendly and welcoming.
Loved the stay. Nice clean rooms. Close to the beach.

Big hugs to both Anita and Khan for being these wonderful hosts. We were a group of 10 and was at Varkala over the long weekend. They made us feel so comfortable and at ease. The collaboration space and yoga place are the best areas for a hangout if in group or alone. They were very informative and helpful about varkala and the places to go. Thanks for this place, what started as a one off group trip has turned into a regular one. Darjeeling cafe nearby is a must visit at night.
Very Good place to stay in Varkala. Had good time der.
In a great location just by Varkala Cliff, this guesthouse has ample communal areas making it a very friendly place to stay
Awesome location and great hospitality :)

Anita was super nice. She really helped us settle in and gave us some great tips on places to eat in the area. The location of the property is spot on: close to shops, restaurants and of course, the beach. The room was basic but the bed was comfy and absolutely spotless. I also enjoyed some chill-out time in their hammocks outside and the top roof terrace. If you're looking for a place to stay in Varkala, Anita and her Dad are super welcoming and make you feel right at home.

Anita is the friendliest and most conscientious Air B and B host we have ever met. From check-in/out to helping arrange our transportation, she was always there to lend a hand. This includes arranging a driver and personally visiting the local post office to ask them to stay open late so our friend could track down a delivery he was expecting before our departure.
Anita's complex is ideally located just off the main strip of shops and restaurants of South Cliff, Varkala. You can walk down to the beach in no time. They have a lovely common outdoor lounge where free tea, coffee and bottled drinking water are available guests. Her friendly rescued dog and cat add to the homey feel. The rooms are tidy and the bathrooms clean. We had a no A/C room and were perfectly comfortable with the overhead fan. The Wifi speed is good as well.
The roof spot for yoga is huge and she can arrange sessions with a teacher. When we were there it was 300 rupees per person. She is in the process of constructing a restaurant space on the grounds which will eventually offer meals and cooking classes.
If you are lucky, her dad may be visiting as well. Interesting, warm, funny and a delight to hang out with as well!

Thank you Anita!
Our family of four hade a great stay at The New White House for two weeks. We appreciated the early communication prior to our departure. We got all the information we needed to get to the house in Varkala Beach. After check-in Anita explained all the important useful facts for newcomers. She also made a nice drawing over the neighbourhood that we used a lot exploring the area. Through Anita we did a number of interesting excursions. We did SUP (stand up paddling ) where se conducted the coaching herself. A lovely three hour paddling on a board out on the "back waters", the last 30 minutes in sun set. We also had a full day excursion, with a private driver, to an Elephant Rehab Center, a jungle walk to a waterfall (Meenmutti) and a nice drive up to a mountain top (Ponmudi) through tea plantations and monkeys jumping over the road.
If you are interested in Yoga, Varkala is the place to be. We had yoga on the rooftop in the mornings (thanks Theresa). We had yoga on the beach and in a few other places.
We hade Ayurveda massage around the corner several times and all feel rejuvenated coming back to our home in Sweden.
We can sincerely recommend Anita and her family to all future guests. You will be good taken care of.
Ann, Fredrik, John and Victoria Stahle

name: Gorgeous 5BHK Luxury villa in heart of Whitefield

reviews.comments: This is the perfect place to stay if you are craving some greenery and space. I stayed with my family after being cooped up for lockdown in a city centre apartment. I wish I could have spent lockdown here - it was amazing! The kids loved the garden and I enjoyed sitting out with them everyday. The house is so stylish - it is a really beautiful space where we felt immediately at home, comfortable and happy. It was the perfect staycation in a time of uncertainty. I would recommend it highly.
The place is very good for a large family, though the advertised number of guests is 10, because it has 5 bedrooms, the place feels large for just 10 people.
Our family of twelve had a relaxing and luxurious staycation at Jawad’s gorgeous  villa. Would definitely recommend!
Good place for a get together

Everything is as advertised, and if anything, the actually location looks even better than the photos at this link.
We were a group of 11 and had a great time here. It's spacious, and feels secluded and away from the city despite being located in the heart of Whitefield.

Mr. Jawad is an excellent host. Very considerate to matters regarding hospitality, comfort, privacy of us guests at his villa. The cleanliness, the tiny bits of curious, decorative items and the lightning imparts a sense of warmth as we walk into the premises. The villa as such feels nothing short of a home.
Mr. Bhima(the caretaker) is very thoughtful. He is co-operative, prompt and courteous. The amount of time and energy spent by the man and his family is maintaining the villa and especially the garden around it is commendable.
#406, Dolsworth colony is a sure shot winner!

Huge 5 bedroom villa, with a lot of open space and privacy in the middle on white field. Our family enjoyed the stay here for 2 days. The caretaker, Bhima is very helpful. The place is a bit hard to find from the road. Few parts of the building could be maintained better, but overall we had a good time staying here.

This villa is a gem. A giant mansion in the middle of a busy center but offers heaps of solititude and peace if you want it. The place is humongous and the rooms are massive, each with its own ensuite.
Basic kitchen amenities available and if you feel something is missing, just Jawad know and he will make it happen from whichever corner of the world he is. There are always small hiccups here and there but that is part of every travel. Bhima, the caretaker is extrmely welcoming, polite and helpful and so are his boys, especially the youngest one. He stole everyone's heart. They live in a cottage next to the house and that in itself is so amazing an experience. The highlights are
1.Tall ceilings and heaps of space
2.Magnificient garden and lawned outdoors over an acre with bird and insect chirps adding that jungle feel to it.
3. All amenities close by and take away food delivered within minutes if you like.
4. Jawad, the host. He is awesome, always listens, checks and actions, if needed. A true gentleman.
5. Bhima, to trouble shoot and run errands.
Overall, a luxury!!!

We stayed here for two days. We used two rooms, and had a dog with us. The house itself is gorgeous. Big lawn, tastefully done interiors.
What’s missing is the a high standard of service (absence of toiletries, basic provisions eg some milk, coffee; bed sheets, dirt in some areas) - partly to do with our own expectations having lived in superbly appointed Airbnb’s around the world, partly to do with this perhaps being a new home on airbnb. I have no doubt it will get better with the service
If you are looking at this place, I’d strongly encourage you to try it - I’ve found the host to be a thoughtful and interested person willing to help; and I have no doubt the experience will improve with the host’s experience on airbnb

The best place I have stayed through ABNB , the host was very understanding and accommodative, love the simplicity of the architecture, the place is well maintained and clean, a word of appreciation for the hosing keeping person, best place for a group in Bangalore within the city... I would highly recommend to others.

primaryHost.about:
Hello! 

My name is Manik, I am Indo - French, and was born and brought up in Bangalore..  Went to college in France, worked there for a bit and decided to move back to India in December of 2014. I now spend time between our guest house and my project, mainly dealing with the development of football in India.

My Father , Bhushan Oberoi, is Indian and is a hotelier by profession. We had 7 European restaurants in Bangalore and now we have Casa Cottage as well as 10 furnished apartments for long term stays.

My mother, Benjamine Oberoi is French and settled here more than 30 years ago. She now dedicates a large amount of her time to social work, where she has been highly recognized by both the Indian and French governments for the work and effort she has put in over the years. For those of you coming to India for social work, thesis on topics that could relate to NGO work, she will be happy to exchange with you and put you in touch with people she knows. 

We got the opportunity to restore a colonial House to its time of glory 15 years ago. We take a lot of pleasure talking and exchanging with our guests.
We love to travel and meet local people so we try to have the same atmosphere we enjoy when we travel around our guest house. 
We travel a lot in India and nearby countries : Sri Lanka, Thailand, Laos, Vietnam , Cambodia,  and many European countries.

Are you Golfers? Bridgers? Then we can have a game together!
